"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-01-18-olympic-gymnast-aly-raisman-espn-broadcasting-role-resume\", \"text\": \"Three-time Olympic gold medalist gymnast Aly Raisman will be joining ESPN as a college gymnastics analyst this season, the network announced on Thursday.  Raisman, who competed in the 2012 London Olympics and the 2016 Rio Olympics, will make her broadcasting debut on Friday, Jan. 19 for the\\u00c2\\u00a0No. 6 Kentucky vs. No. 8 LSU meet on SEC Network.  Raisman will be joined by three-time Olympic gymnast John Roethlisberger on the call for ESPN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s coverage on Friday night.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m excited to be part of the ESPN gymnastics team and share my passion and love for the sport in a new way,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Raisman said,via an ESPN press release. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been so fun to watch these incredible athletes and see how much gymnastics continues to grow. I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m looking forward to this next chapter and the opportunity to try something different within the sport.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The 29-year-oldtoldPEOPLEthat she is also \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cnervous\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d for the opportunity because she wants to do a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cgood job\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in this \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009creally cool new chapter\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in her life.  Raisman was notably the captain of Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFierce Five\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d group, which included Gabby Douglas, McKayla Maroney, Kyla Ross and Jordyn Wieber.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Madison Williams is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated, where she specializes in tennis but covers a wide range of sports from a national perspective. Before joining SI in 2022, Williams worked at The Sporting News. Having graduated from Augustana College, she completed a master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in sports media at Northwestern University.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"